// 13: AUTO-CALIBRATION
`<div class="s-tag fade">Auto-calibration</div>
<div class="s-h1 fade d1">Karpathy's autoresearch loop</div>
<div class="s-sub fade d2">After 1st PI (10 weeks) the team has &#x2265; 20 confirmed CW records. Agent optimizes heuristics overnight.</div>
<div class="cols fade d3">
<div class="col">
<div class="fm" style="font-size:11px;border-left-color:var(--or)"><b>One file, one metric, one loop:</b>

Target:  cw_heuristics.yaml
Metric:  MAD (mean absolute deviation)
Dir:     lower
Budget:  50 experiments (~2h)
Memory:  git log

Loop:
1. Load history + results
2. Propose ONE change
3. Commit &#x2192; evaluate &#x2192; keep/revert
4. Repeat 50x</div>
</div>
<div class="col">
<div class="sc g" style="margin-bottom:8px"><div class="sc-t">Benefit</div><div class="sc-l">MAD reduction: <b>6.5%</b>. More accurate reports without manual discussion at retro.</div></div>
<div class="sc c" style="margin-bottom:8px"><div class="sc-t">Monte Carlo validation</div><div class="sc-l">1,000 scenarios, 31,041 records. Calibrates 5 signal weights (assignee, pr_author, commit_author, pr_reviewer, issue_comment).</div></div>
<div class="sc o" style="margin-bottom:8px"><div class="sc-t">Safety</div><div class="sc-l">Agent <b>must not edit the calibrator</b> (calibrate_signals.py). Synthetic corpus + MAD cost function live in one file — separation by structure.</div></div>
<div class="sc a"><div class="sc-t">Real-data phase</div><div class="sc-l">Synthetic MC runs anytime. Real-data adapter (from PI retro) only after the 1st closed PI.</div></div>
</div></div>`,

